image_analysis.description: A photograph of a luxurious interior room. The room features dark wood parquet flooring and a large built-in wooden bookcase filled with numerous books. On top of the bookcase sits a large, light-colored sculpture of two animals (possibly wolves or dogs) howling. Behind the sculpture is a wall covered in antiqued or distressed mirrored panels that reflect the ornate ceiling and other parts of the room. To the left of the bookcase, there is a tall blue and white porcelain vase and a chair with leopard-print upholstery. In the background, blue and white porcelain figurines are visible on a shelf.
image_analysis.layout: Interior shot with a central focus on a bookcase and sculpture against a mirrored wall.

stamps_or_markings: Bates stamp 'EFTA00000993' in the bottom right corner

notes: The image is a photograph included in a document production, identified by the Bates number EFTA00000993. The text on the book spines is visible but too small and varied to extract reliably without high-resolution crops.
